{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17488710","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17488710"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:53:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:53:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"514"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"514","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/514"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.35,0.03,0.52,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"514"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76742"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"514","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/514"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"514"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62235"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"1144"},{"type":"tags","id":"2273"},{"type":"tags","id":"3583"},{"type":"tags","id":"3856"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1041"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1108"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76742","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76742"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA previously well 62-year-old man presents with a one month history of hoarse voice. He has a 35 pack-year smoking history and drinks three standard drinks a day. The only abnormality on physical examination is that shown in the photograph (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["MRI brain","Head and neck CT","Carotid ultrasound","Chest X-ray","Thyroid scintigraphy"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe image show a right ptosis and miosis (constricted pupil), which is consistent with Horner\u0027s syndrome. Horner\u0027s syndrome involves an interruption of the sympathetic supply to the eye and is likely secondary to a pancoast tumour of the lung in this case. The hoarse voice could be due to a vocal cord palsy - the result of an apical tumour invading the recurrent laryngeal nerve. The most appropriate investigation in the first instance would be a \u003Cstrong\u003Echest X-ray\u003C/strong\u003E. This could be followed by a CT chest if an abnormality was found.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnMRI brain may be ordered to assess for cavernous sinus lesions, however this is less likely in the absence of other cranial nerve signs. Head and neck CT may identify base of skull tumours, however lung cancer is most suggested by this case. Carotid ultrasound for carotid dissection is inappropriate as this diagnosis is less likely in the absence of pain. Thyroid scintigraphy for a goitre causing Horner\u0027s syndrome is very uncommon, particularly in the absence of a goitre on physical examination.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A hoarse voice in a smoker must always raise concerns about the possibility of lung cancer."],"references":["Martin TJ. Horner Syndrome: A Clinical Review. ACS Chem Neurosci. 2018 Feb 21;9(2):177-186. doi: 10.1021/acschemneuro.7b00405. Epub 2017 Dec 20. PMID: 29260849.","Reede DL, Garcon E, Smoker WR, Kardon R. Horner\u0027s syndrome: clinical and radiographic evaluation. Neuroimaging Clin N Am. 2008 May;18(2):369-85, xi. doi: 10.1016/j.nic.2007.11.003. PMID: 18466837.","Almog Y, Gepstein R, Kesler A. Diagnostic value of imaging in horner syndrome in adults. J Neuroophthalmol. 2010 Mar;30(1):7-11. doi: 10.1097/WNO.0b013e3181ce1a12. PMID: 20182199.","Walker L, French S. Horner\u0027s Syndrome: A Case Report and Review of the Pathophysiology and Clinical Features. West Indian Med J. 2014 Jun;63(3):278-80. doi: 10.7727/wimj.2014.004. Epub 2014 Jul 17. PMID: 25314289; PMCID: PMC4663911."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62235"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"514"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20062"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"20062","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20062"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/68b711c0-8725-41d5-b192-87f00b0785d0.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/68b711c0-8725-41d5-b192-87f00b0785d0.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":304}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62235","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62235"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-04T19:53:29+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-04T19:53:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"514"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76742"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","